
---

## Step 3: Open Terminal in PyCharm

In PyCharm, click **Terminal** at the bottom or press `Alt+F12`

---

## Step 4: Run Git Commands

Copy and paste these commands one by one:

```bash
# Check current directory (should be your project folder)
pwd

# Initialize git repository
git init

# Check what files will be added
git status

# Add all files (except those in .gitignore)
git add .

# Check again (should NOT show .pkl files)
git status

# Commit the files
git commit -m "Initial commit: Breast cancer detection research prototype"

# Add your GitHub repository as remote (replace YOUR_USERNAME)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/breast-cancer-detection-ai.git

# Push to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main